transcripts.text: How you doing?  Why do you tell me about what you like about President Trump?
What I like about- If you're gonna bring him over here, bring him and say what he said.  Okay.  He is a race fader.  Black Trump is supporting President Trump.
Hey, hey, hey.

Well, see, Malcolm X said that any black man that votes for a Democrat is a traitor to his race.  Yahweh bin Yahweh said the same thing.  So did Elijah Muhammad.  Martin Luther King was a Republican.  The Black Lives Matter leader even said the same thing.  So any black man that's out here supporting the Democrats is an absolute distractor.
I don't like the establishment Democrats.  I'm asking what has President Trump done for you?
Oh, you didn't ask me that at first.  You said, what do I like?
I said, what do you like about Trump?

Oh, yeah, right.  What I like about Trump is first he got elected.  That's the first thing I like about him.  Second thing I like about him is that he's getting ready to put Hillary and all of the bastards that put 1.2 million black men in jail in jail themselves for being murderous traitors to America and the black man.
In fairness, that was Bill Clinton, but yeah, you're right about that.

Bill Clinton and Hillary, she was the one that said black people are predators, but they don't see that.  She was the one that said she used to have black slaves in Arkansas in the governor's mansion.  I got on camera saying that with 40 black men standing behind her with jail outfits on as if there was no white people in jail in Arkansas.
Do you think President Trump has been strong on race?
He's been beautiful in race because you know what?  You're here at the Central Park Five?
Yeah.  That he put a full-page ad out?

You want me to answer?  You want me to answer?  Oh, here's my answer to that.  Obama got in.  He let every East Indian, Arab, and Pakistani who sold drugs to the black men who were selling drugs over here in America.  He let them go.  And they were also murdering black people.  He let them out of Gitmo.  He didn't let one black man out, like Larry Hoover, Big Meech, Tim Brown, Rick Brownlee.  He didn't let none of them out.  He didn't let Boom out.  He didn't let out none of them.  Trump gets in.  Trump gets in.  Trump gets in, and what does he do?  He passes the Prison Reform Act.  Now, Bo Dilley, one of the biggest drug dealers, is out.  Now, you got Boom, which is my brother.  He's out.  I go to the halfway house, and all of the brothers who was in jail that Trump let out, the CO said, Hey, man, that's the brother that helped Trump get y'all out.  And they all said, Black for Trump!
Yeah!  Are you talking about the first step back?
I know the Prison Reform Act, sir.  Yeah, or First Step Act, whatever you...
I think that was a good thing.
Yeah, that is a good thing.  Where was Obama on that?  Hillary and Bill Clinton put 1.2...
We agree, but I was asking...
You said what's good about it.  You said what's good about it.  He talked about the Central Park Five.  Now, listen to the question that he said.
I was talking about...

You're saying that Trump is not racist, and we're talking about what he put out and what he's doing now.  All of my brothers who got out of jail, who did not deserve to be there, that's what I'm talking about.
What about the Central Park Five?

2 million black men in jail... That's what I'm against.  I'm answering the question the way I answer it.  The Central Park Five, I really didn't study them or find out what they did or didn't do, so I cannot respond to that.  But I can respond to the fact that he let out black men out of jail when that bastard Obama put us in jail and kept us there.  So I don't want to hear all of that.  He is nothing but a traitor to his race.  Obama!  Obama, I want me to get it clear, Obama crossed out of there.
But we agree, but we agree about that.  Okay, so let's...
You support who?  The Democrat?  Who do I support?  I support Bernie Sanders.  Bernie Sanders, who's a Cherokee Indian who had us in slavery, of course.
Bernie Sanders is a Cherokee Indian?  He is, he says he is.
His wife is, but that ain't the...
What are you talking about?
The point I'm making is...
No, you're talking about Elizabeth Warren.
No, Bernie Sanders, I'm talking about him, sir.  You just don't know the history.
No, you're talking about Elizabeth Warren.
Okay, but Bernie Sanders is a communist and a socialist, which means give all our money to them when they're supposed to be paying tribute to America.
Our brothers are on the street.  You don't mind corporate wealth?  You don't mind the corporate welfare?
on the street who are Vietnam vets, black men.  But then they want to let all of them in from other countries to get in and get free housing.
